  "text": "User intervention is relied upon in a clustering approach in [CITATION_1] where the authors employ similarity methods with semi-supervised fuzzy clustering for semi-automatic image annotation. The premise is that user intervention may be required to help accurately define clusters by specifying pairwise relationships (must-link, cannot-link) between instances which are at the borders of automatically defined clusters. This method relies on the assumption that users can easily specify the pairwise constraints on images and that after specifying such constraints the clusters in question are better separated. The centroids of strong clusters are found by isolating and purging spurious small clusters. The method is compared with two other clustering methods: CA and K-means. The authors conclude that as long as the user intervention is minimal and simple, important information can be gleaned from this step.",
